    <item>
      <title>Don’t prematurely obsess on a single “big problem” or “big theory”</title>
      <link>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/orig/dont-prematurely-obsess-on-a-single-big-problem-or-big-theory/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 06 May 2007 19:04:21 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/orig/dont-prematurely-obsess-on-a-single-big-problem-or-big-theory/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/zh/dont-prematurely-obsess-on-a-single-big-problem-or-big-theory.zh/&#34;&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;div&#xA;  class=&#34;link-card group relative my-3 w-full overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-[var(--lc-border,rgba(15,23,42,0.12))] bg-[var(--lc-bg,var(--card-bg,var(--surface,#ffffff))))] transition-shadow duration-150 hover:shadow-[var(--lc-shadow-hover,0_14px_30px_-18px_rgba(15,23,42,0.35))]&#34;&#xA;  data-url=&#34;https://terrytao.wordpress.com/career-advice/dont-prematurely-obsess-on-a-single-big-problem-or-big-theory/&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link-card__fallback block px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--lc-url,var(--link-color,#0e6a85))] underline-offset-4 hover:underline&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://terrytao.wordpress.com/career-advice/dont-prematurely-obsess-on-a-single-big-problem-or-big-theory/&#34;&#xA;    target=&#34;_blank&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&#xA;  &gt;&#xA;    https://terrytao.wordpress.com/career-advice/dont-prematurely-obsess-on-a-single-big-problem-or-big-theory/&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;dont-prematurely-obsess-on-a-single-big-problem-or-big-theory&#34;&gt;Don’t prematurely obsess on a single &amp;ldquo;big problem&amp;rdquo; or &amp;ldquo;big theory&amp;rdquo;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Millions long for immortality who do not know what to do with themselves on a rainy Sunday afternoon.&#xA;— Susan Ertz, &amp;ldquo;Anger in the Sky&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;There is a particularly dangerous occupational hazard in this subject: one can become focused, to the exclusion of other mathematical activity (and in extreme cases, on non-mathematical activity also), on a single really difficult problem in a field (or on some grand unifying theory) before one is really ready (both in terms of mathematical preparation, and also in terms of one&amp;rsquo;s career) to devote so much of one&amp;rsquo;s research time to such a project. This is doubly true if one has not yet &lt;strong&gt;learnt the limitations of one&amp;rsquo;s tools&lt;/strong&gt; or acquired a healthy &lt;strong&gt;scepticism of one&amp;rsquo;s own work&lt;/strong&gt;, as this can lead to the humiliating spectacle of proudly announcing a major breakthrough on a well known problem, only to withdraw the preprint shortly afterwards after serious flaws (often arising from pushing a method well beyond its known limits, and encounting obstructions beyond those limits that were known to the experts) are pointed out in the manuscript.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Be sceptical of your own work</title>
      <link>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/orig/be-sceptical-of-your-own-work/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 06 May 2007 18:57:36 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/orig/be-sceptical-of-your-own-work/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/zh/be-sceptical-of-your-own-work.zh/&#34;&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;div&#xA;  class=&#34;link-card group relative my-3 w-full overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-[var(--lc-border,rgba(15,23,42,0.12))] bg-[var(--lc-bg,var(--card-bg,var(--surface,#ffffff))))] transition-shadow duration-150 hover:shadow-[var(--lc-shadow-hover,0_14px_30px_-18px_rgba(15,23,42,0.35))]&#34;&#xA;  data-url=&#34;https://terrytao.wordpress.com/career-advice/be-sceptical-of-your-own-work/&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link-card__fallback block px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--lc-url,var(--link-color,#0e6a85))] underline-offset-4 hover:underline&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://terrytao.wordpress.com/career-advice/be-sceptical-of-your-own-work/&#34;&#xA;    target=&#34;_blank&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&#xA;  &gt;&#xA;    https://terrytao.wordpress.com/career-advice/be-sceptical-of-your-own-work/&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;be-sceptical-of-your-own-work&#34;&gt;Be sceptical of your own work&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;An expert is a man who has made all the mistakes, which can be made, in a very narrow field.&#xA;— Niels Bohr&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;If you unexpectedly find a problem solving itself almost effortlessly, and you can&amp;rsquo;t quite see why, you should try to analyse your solution more sceptically.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Early</title>
      <link>https://linguage.github.io/paul_graham/essays_en/early/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://linguage.github.io/paul_graham/essays_en/early/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;→ &lt;a href=&#34;https://linguage.github.io/paul_graham/essays_zh/early/&#34;&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div&#xA;  class=&#34;link-card group relative my-3 w-full overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-[var(--lc-border,rgba(15,23,42,0.12))] bg-[var(--lc-bg,var(--card-bg,var(--surface,#ffffff))))] transition-shadow duration-150 hover:shadow-[var(--lc-shadow-hover,0_14px_30px_-18px_rgba(15,23,42,0.35))]&#34;&#xA;  data-url=&#34;https://www.paulgraham.com/early.html&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link-card__fallback block px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--lc-url,var(--link-color,#0e6a85))] underline-offset-4 hover:underline&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://www.paulgraham.com/early.html&#34;&#xA;    target=&#34;_blank&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&#xA;  &gt;&#xA;    https://www.paulgraham.com/early.html&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;early&#34;&gt;Early&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;October 2020&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;One of the biggest things holding people back from doing great work is the fear of making something lame. And this fear is not an irrational one. Many great projects go through a stage early on where they don&amp;rsquo;t seem very impressive, even to their creators. You have to push through this stage to reach the great work that lies beyond. But many people don&amp;rsquo;t. Most people don&amp;rsquo;t even reach the stage of making something they&amp;rsquo;re embarrassed by, let alone continue past it. They&amp;rsquo;re too frightened even to start.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
